<TEXT>
the soviet union and china agreed sunday to hold 
talks in november to discuss reductions in their armed forces along 
the chinesesoviet border the soviet news agency tass reported 
tass in a dispatch from paris said soviet foreign minister 
eduard shevardnadze and chinese foreign minister qian qichen agreed 
at a meeting that the talks would be held in moscow 
shevardnadze and quian are in paris participating in an 
international peace conference on cambodia 
tass said the two ministers noted with satisfaction that since 
the normalization of sovietchinese relations at the summit meeting 
in beijing last may useful work has been done to translate into 
life the impressive potential of cooperation between the soviet 
union and china in economics science and culture 
it said sundays agreement calls for holding the first meeting 
of diplomatic and military experts in moscow next november to 
consider cuts in the armed forces in areas adjacent to the 
sovietchinese border and confidencebuilding measures in the 
military sphere 
tass reported the two countries will hold a fourth round of 
talks on border issues in beijing in october 
it described the ministers meeting as businesslike and 
constructive held in a friendly atmosphere 
</TEXT>
