lebanons ambassador to iraq was quoted 
sunday as confirming that christian army commander gen michel aoun 
has acquired missiles and other weapons from iraq to bolster his 
war effort against syrian forces 
artillery duels raged between syrian and christian forces 
setting huge fires in residential districts in the citys moslem 
and christian sectors 
four people were killed and 52 were wounded in the shelling that 
began after sundown and continued for nine hours 
the casualties raised the toll to 506 killed and 2118 wounded 
since the current round of fighting in lebanons 14yearold civil 
war broke out march 8 pitting aouns 20000 troops against the 
syrians and their druse moslem allies 
fire brigades in east and west beirut said they were unable to 
battle the fires which gutted several apartment buildings and 
gasoline stations because of water shortages 
police said syrian gunners blasted aouns presidential palace in 
suburban baabda east of beirut with rockets and that aoun was in 
the underground bunker of the twostory building 
several shells exploded around the office of syrianbacked 
acting prime minister salim hoss officials said hoss was at his 
home about a mile away from his office 
aoun heads a christian military cabinet vying for legitimacy 
with hoss syrianbacked moslem government 
shells also hit near the buildings housing the associated press 
united press international reuters and the agence francepresse 
news agencies near west beiruts hamra commercial thoroughfare 
there were no casualties among journalists 
yes lebanon does possess frog7 missiles supplied by iraq 
